  Locus:
    Page: 81
    Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Death
---
The knowledge that we will die burns out our attachments to the dignified
madness of our socially constructed existence. Death is an ally that helps
us to release our clinging to social position, material accumulation, and
superficial desires as a source of ultimate security.
